"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470509","Department for International Development","false","2016-03-21","<p>The UK is gravely concerned about the ongoing political and human rights crisis in Burundi. DFID has provided technical support, in the form of secondment of experts, to support and strengthen the capacity of UN agencies working in Burundi, and has deployed a humanitarian adviser to the region in support of the response and to monitor funding provided so far.</p><p>DFID has provided £21.15 million since April 2015 to support shelter, food, healthcare and livelihoods assistance for Burundian refugees in Tanzania and Rwanda. DFID is also supporting refugees in the DRC and Uganda through existing programmes and the provision of technical advice. DFID offices across the region are working closely to monitor the situation, review preparedness activities and provide humanitarian support.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2016-03-21T15:12:10.733Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470509/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470509/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470509/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-03-14","Burundi: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what plans her Department has for post-conflict assistance in Burundi.","false","Biography information for Jo Cox","Batley and Spen","Jo Cox","30922"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470510","Department for International Development","false","2016-03-17","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I provided on 17 March to Question number 30955</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2016-03-17T15:35:39.45Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470510/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470510/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470510/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-03-14","Israel: Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, which (a) fixed and (b) mobile structures funded by her Department in Area C of the Occupied Palestinian Territory have been (i) demolished and (ii) confiscated by the Israeli authorities in (A) 2015 and (B) 2016.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","30875"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470512","Department for International Development","false","2016-03-17","<p>No UK funded structures have been demolished or confiscated in Area C in 2015 or 2016. A number of EU ECHO-funded structures have been demolished in recent months. The UK contributes to the EU budget as a whole, not individual instruments within it. The UK’s share on EU expenditure in EU instruments is approximately 15%.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2016-03-17T15:33:03.597Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470512/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470512/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470512/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-03-14","Israel: Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what estimate she has made of the value of UK-funded structures that were demolished or confiscated in Area C of the Occupied Palestinian Territory in (a) 2015 and (b) 2016.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","30873"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470513","Department for International Development","false","2016-03-17","<p>DFID is undertaking a number of reviews, which aim to look across our portfolio to build the most effective response to deliver the Spending Review, the UK Aid Strategy and the Strategic Defence and Security Review. These include a review of the research portfolio, a Civil Society Partnership Review, a Multilateral Aid Review and a Bilateral Aid Review (BAR). The outcome of these reviews will collectively determine DFID’s approach to delivering the UK Aid Strategy over the period of the Spending Review.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2016-03-17T15:33:43.597Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470513/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470513/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470513/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-03-14","Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what her Department's decision making process is on the (a) provision and (b) removal of (i) bilateral and (ii) other aid assistance programmes.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","30874"
