ording system.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2016-05-12T10:02:45.3Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470526/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470526/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470526/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-03-14","Prisoners: Repatriation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many foreign national offenders from each other EU member state serving a custodial sentence in the UK in each of the last 10 years have been transferred to serve the remainder of their sentence in another EU member state.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","30998"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470528","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-03-22","<p>The Ministry of Justice Court Proceedings Database does not hold the nationality of offenders convicted of criminal offences in England and Wales. Obtaining this information would incur disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>As announced in the Prime Minister’s speech on 8 February, my officials have been working closely with the Home Office to introduce a legal requirement for defendants appearing in court to provide their name, date of birth and nationality. This will enable earlier identification of foreign national offenders and help with the removals process.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","30997","2016-03-22T14:59:57.647Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470528/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470528/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470528/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-03-14","EU Nationals: Convictions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many EU nationals were convicted of a criminal offence in the UK in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","31025"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470529","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-04-13","<p>Information on Foreign national offenders is regularly published on gov.uk website on the following link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/offender-management-statistics-quarterly-july-to-september-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/offender-management-statistics-quarterly-july-to-september-2015</a></p><p> </p><p>The specific information requested can be found in the attached annex.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2016-04-13T10:34:46.313Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470529/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470529/answer","31039 Annex - Sentenced Foreign Nationals.xls","31039 Annex - Sentenced Foreign Nationals.xls","Sentenced Foreign Nationals","Sentenced Foreign Nationals","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470529/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-03-14","Sentencing: Foreign Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many foreign national offenders of each nationality are serving custodial sentences of (a) less than six months, (b) six months to one year, (c) one year to two years, (d) two years to three years, (e) three years to four years, (f) four years to five years, (g) five years to 10 years and (h) more than 10 years.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","31039"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470530","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-03-24","<p>Records indicate that my Department has received and approved a total of 31 applications for public interest immunity in the last five years.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2016-03-24T12:44:12.947Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470530/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470530/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470530/answer","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/470530/answer/previousversion/51996","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-03-14","Immunity Certificates: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many public interest immunity applications her Department has (a) received and (b) approved in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Gavin Robinson","Belfast East","Gavin Robinson","30968"
