"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459838","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-24","<p>These issues are being considered as part of Charter Review. The Government will set out its proposals in the forthcoming White Paper.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe","HL6939 ; HL6940 ; HL6943","2016-03-24T10:33:46.533Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459838/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459838/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459838/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-03-11","BBC","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the case for the BBC's service licences being reviewed and strengthened by an independent regulator at an early date.","false","Biography information for Lord Lester of Herne Hill",,"Lord Lester of Herne Hill","HL6941"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459840","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-24","<p>The BBC Charter Review Consultation Paper, published in July 2015, set out the issues for consideration in Charter Review, including questions about how the BBC is funded. The Government will set out its proposals in the forthcoming White Paper, but remains clear that the licence fee is a tax and therefore should ultimately be decided by Ministers. The level of the licence fee will be agreed once questions on the BBC's scope and purposes, have been agreed.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2016-03-24T12:33:08.427Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459840/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459840/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459840/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-03-11","Television: Licensing","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the appropriate level for the BBC licence fee and of the case for that level being recommended by an independent regulator.","false","Biography information for Lord Lester of Herne Hill",,"Lord Lester of Herne Hill","HL6942"
