resources/461210/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/461210/answer","acas-enquiries-topics.xls","acas-enquiries-topics.xls","ACAS enquiries by call topics","ACAS enquiries by call topics","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/461210/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-03-11","ACAS","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many enquires Acas received from (a) employees and (b) employers (i) from each employment sector and (ii) relating to each topic on its database in each year since 2009-10.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","30831"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/461212","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-18","<p>The only referrals recorded by Acas are those made to the various enforcement bodies that have been set up to protect vulnerable workers. Acas has made these referrals since taking over the Pay and Work Rights Helpline in April 2015. The number of referrals made to each enforcement body since April 2015 is set out in the following table:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>HMRC</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>EAS</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>HSE</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>GLA</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>April to Feb Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>1,667</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>229</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>111</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2,018</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: Acas</p><ul><li><strong>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) </strong>– calls on potential enforcement of the National Minimum Wage</li><li><strong>Employment Agency Standards Inspectorate</strong> – calls on potential enforcement of employment agency legislation (except Agency Worker Regulations)</li><li><strong>Gangmasters Licensing Authority (GLA)</strong> – calls relating to agency workers in agriculture, horticulture, shellfish gathering or associated processing and packaging</li><li><strong>Health and Safety Executive (HSE)</strong> – calls on potential enforcement of working time issues, including enforcement of maximum weekly working hours</li></ul>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-03-18T16:03:15.857Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/461212/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/461212/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/461212/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-03-11","ACAS: Public Bodies","1","Hous