"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459435","Home Office","false","2016-03-15","<p>The Home Office routinely publishes figures on the total number of foreign national offenders that have been deported. The figures can be found on the following link:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/immigration-statistics-october-to-december-2015-data-tables</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-03-15T14:28:18.407Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459435/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459435/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459435/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-03-10","Offenders: Deportation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people with a criminal conviction have been deported in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","30746"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459436","Home Office","false","2016-03-15","<p>The Home Office led Emergency Services Mobile Communications Programme (ESMCP) is in ongoing discussions with EE as the supplier of Network Services for the new Emergency Services Network (ESN).</p><p>The Emergency Services Mobile Communications Programme’s Extended Area Service is planning a number of new mast sites across the UK. The location of new mast sites will be announced in due course, once all the relevant permissions have been granted.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","30753","2016-03-15T15:16:10.5Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459436/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459436/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459436/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-03-10","Emergency Services Network: Aerials","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether her Department plans to announce new mast sites for the Emergency Service Mobile Communications Programme's Extended Areas Service project.","false","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael","30736"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459437","Home Office","false","2016-03-15","<p>The Home Office does not hold this information in the format requested. It could only be obtained at disproportionate cost, through the interrogation of individual case records.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-03-15T14:28:55.95Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459437/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459437/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459437/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-03-10","Visas: Ministers of Religion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 9 March 2016 to Question 29595, what the reasons were for refusal of the Tier 2 (Minister of Religion) Visas.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","30743"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459438","Department for International Development","false","2016-03-17","<p>The UK is a leader in climate risk insurance and is committed to contributing to meeting the G7 “InsuResilience” collective target set out in the Elmau declaration of helping up to an additional 400 million people in the most vulnerable developing countries to gain access to climate risk insurance by 2020.</p><p>Recent UK support for the provision of climate risk insurance includes contributions of up to £100m to African Risk Capacity (ARC), up to £15m for the Pacific Catastrophe Risk Assessment and Financing Initiative, £5m to help developing countries with disaster contingency planning backed by risk finance, £3m of technical support to the Government of the Philippines to help them implement their financial protection and insurance strategy, and £1.4m to support livestock insurance for pastoralists in Kenya.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2016-03-17T15:27:15.307Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459438/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459438/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459438/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-03-10","Developing Countries: Climate Change","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps the UK is taking to support the provision of climate risk insurance to people who are most vulnerable to the impact of climate change; and how much funding she plans to allocate to such support.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","30717"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459439","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-03-16","All employers are obligated to pay a minimum of the new National Living Wage from April 2016.","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-03-16T14:10:58.257Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459439/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459439/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459439/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-03-10","Ministry of Justice: Cleaning Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 25 February 2016 to Question 28610, which outsourced providers his Department uses for cleaning services; and if he will request information from those providers on the rate of pay for cleaners providing services for his Department.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","30745"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459440","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-03-17","<p>Family Courts are subject to Security Standards, which provide a framework for security measures at each individual court.</p><p> </p><p>Security standards are under continual review by each local court. In practice this comprises each court undertaking reviews of all significant incidents trends/lessons learned, findings from risk assessments, engagement with inter-agency partners, feedback following complaints and regular local inspections. This is to ensure adequate protection measures are in place to protect court users.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2016-03-17T11:43:07.267Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459440/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459440/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459440/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-03-10","Family Courts: Domestic Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 25 February 2016 to Question 27240, on family courts: domestic violence, when his Department last reviewed the security standards referred to in that Answer.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","30621"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459441","Prime Minister","false","2016-03-15","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to the hon. Member for Leicester South (Mr Ashworth) on 29 February 2016, UIN 28380.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron","30651","2016-03-15T17:14:14.337Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459441/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459441/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/459441/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2016-03-10","UK Membership of EU: Referendums","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, how many special advisers have notified the Prime Minister's Principal Secretary that they are supporting ministers who are campaigning against the Government's position on the EU referendum.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","30652"
